This paper proposes a method for arbitrary style transfer using deep learning techniques, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of adversarial networks for regularization is also a common technique in deep learning, which could place the paper in the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of a mask module, which could suggest a focus on graphics (cs.GR) or multimedia (cs.MM). Overall, the paper's focus on image stylization and deep learning techniques suggests that it is most likely to belong to the cs.CV sub-category, followed by cs.AI and cs.LG.
